Writing rules for the OWL-Lite nclos
....................................

The result of the independence between the rule and the object system
in the NCLosEmacs design is that rules are written the same way whether
for the default nclos or the OWL-Lite nclos.  *Note Writing Rules with
Patterns in the default nclos::, and *Note Writing Rules with RHSes in
the Default Nclos::.

   The scope of the LHS operators is expanded in the OWL-Lite nclos as
it supports inheritance. Hence the `all-in, some-in, oone-in, none-in'
patterns now select all instances of the mentioned class _and_ of all
its subclasses recursively.


