4.4 Session logs
================

A complete session log is maintained in a special Emacs buffer named
`*nclose-log*'.  This buffer keeps track of the inference progress from
the initial knowcess command.  The buffer is erased with each reset
session command issued by the user.

   Note that logging is implemented as a specific aspect layer in the
`advice.el' file, *Note Aspect Oriented Programming::.  It is then easy
to switch logging on or off by simply enabling or disabling this
particular layer in the file.  In addition, more detailed levels of
trace are simply implemented by creating new advising functions for
events of interest in this layer.


